comment:
He may very possibly be a narcissist. (Scientific research has shown more often men are narcissists than women). So that's a possibility.
She might very well be a narcissist. That's a possibility.
For sure, they both are either good at being dramatic, good at lying, or both, by nature of their livelihoods. So it's complicated.
For sure, we don't know the entirety of their relationship between them. We're not there 24 hours a day, like they were around each other. Relationships are very involving.
How old is Johnny?
How old is Amber?
I think he's older. He may have had a lot of time to fine tune himself, to either emotionally mature or just maybe refine his deceit "game."  It could go either way. There's at least definitely a Daddy Dom Little Girl Sub aspect to them. A lot of themes of power, control, and dominance, are present in their conversation.
It could also be Amber has a mental health condition. (Maybe Johnny needs therapy also to be atttracted to, or attract, these kinds of partners. He's definitely dealing with some attachment  issues.) She may have borderline disorder, bipolar disorder, or other neurological disorders. She may need medical help. Robert Downey Jr. was a better person after being diagnosed with Bipolar disorder. He went on to make the Ironman movies. As for the lives of celebrities and their public personas, these public personas are only their avatars. They may agree with or claim or say things, in the public arena, often times, which may only benefit or brighten their avatars. These celebrities may, in private, say or act in ways that are slightly different from their public avatars or wildly unrecognizable from their public avatars. Each celebrity makes that decision. But we, the audience, may never know. Unless we get up close to these real people ourselves.
It's definitely hard to see a beloved friend go through something intense, and having to doubt, even for a second, whether we really knew them at all.
Prestige, fame, money-- being a celebrity. In terms of relationships (even the relationship one has with oneself! Or one's past!), I can imagine, it can be really hard.
